manities  Music, Film, and Audio'),(998,'The Fiction of Relationship',1,1,'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ssu8GN8UHhM','https://www.coursera.org/course/relationship',10,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:36','2013-04-29 06:43:37','coursera_relationship','What is the nature of our relationship to others and the world?  How can literature help us see these relationships more clearly? This course seeks to explore such questions through adventurous readings of ten great works of narrative fiction from the 18th to the 20th century.','Humanities '),(999,'Science from Superheroes to Global Warming',1,1,'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sITa8jb2ji0','https://www.coursera.org/course/scientificthinking',NULL,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:36','2013-04-29 06:43:37','coursera_scientificthinking','Explore how science works and what constitutes \"good\" science through case studies drawn from a wide spectrum of people\'s experience, for example superheros, movies, and real world issues such as global warming. ','Energy & Earth Sciences'),(1000,'Useful Genetics',1,1,'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jHT3pAgAbFE','https://www.coursera.org/course/usefulgenetics',10,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:36','2013-04-29 06:43:37','coursera_usefulgenetics','This course will give you a thorough understanding of gene function and inheritance, and will enable you to apply this understanding to real-world issues, both personal and societal.','Health & Society Biology & Life Sciences'),(1001,'Archaeology\'s Dirty Little Secrets',1,1,'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=avYqKf1ff08','https://www.coursera.org/course/secrets',8,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:36','2013-04-29 06:43:37','coursera_secrets','Admit it — you wanted to be an archaeologist when you grew up...  This course builds on that enthusiasm, while radically expanding your notions about just what archaeology is and just what archaeologists do. \n ','Humanities '),(1002,'Algebra',1,1,'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XImyLldzvHw','https://www.coursera.org/course/algebra',NULL,NULL,'2