nsonatas',5,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:42','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_beethovensonatas','A series of lectures on one of the greatest bodies of music ever composed, from the point of view of a performer. Each lecture will explore a different facet of the music; all will attempt to locate the source of the tremendous psychological power of Beethoven’s music.','Humanities  Music, Film, and Audio'),(1158,'From the Repertoire: Western Music History through Performance',1,1,NULL,'https://www.coursera.org/course/musichistoryperforms',7,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:42','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_musichistoryperforms','This course will focus on six important works from the Western classical-music repertoire that represent different eras and genres throughout history. We\'ll observe performances of this music recorded at Curtis, and our interactive discussions will explore each work’s historical context, musical significance, and compositional design.','Humanities  Music, Film, and Audio'),(1159,'Fundamentals of Rehearsing Music Ensembles',1,1,NULL,'https://www.coursera.org/course/music-ensembles',8,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:42','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_music-ensembles','Learn and practice the basic principles of running an effective music ensemble rehearsal.  Techniques and strategies are applicable to a variety of ensembles, including bands, orchestras, choirs, and chamber groups.','Music, Film, and Audio'),(1160,'Metadata: Organizing and Discovering Information',1,1,NULL,'https://www.coursera.org/course/metadata',8,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:42','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_metadata','Metadata is an unsung hero of the modern world, the plumbing that makes the information age possible. This course describes how Metadata is used as an information tool for the Web, for databases, and for the software and computing applications around us.','Information, Tech & Design'),(1161,'Epidemiology: The Basic Science of Public Health',1,1,NULL,'https://www.coursera.org/course/epidemiology',6,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:42','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_epidemiology','This course explores public health—both locally and globally—through the lens of epidemiology.','Health & Society'),(1162,'Desarrollo rápido de productos innovadores para mercados emergentes',1,1,'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ase9c_VE3JA','https://www.coursera.org/course/innovacion',6,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:42','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_innovacion','Entender las metodologías para la innovación de productos para mercados emergentes.  Las metodologías son:  1) megatendencias sociales, tecnológicas y del comportamiento del consumidor 2) JTBD y 3) Matriz Morfológica.','Economics & Finance Business & Management'),(1163,'Democratic Development',1,1,NULL,'https://www.coursera.org/course/democraticdev',10,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:42','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_democraticdev','Gain an understanding of the political, social, cultural, economic, institutional and international factors that foster and obstruct the development and consolidation of democracy. It is hoped that students in developing or prospective democracies will use the theories, ideas, and lessons in the class to help build or improve democracy in their own countries.','Humanities  Social Sciences'),(1164,'Write Like Mozart: An Introduction to Classical Music Composition',1,1,NULL,'https://www.coursera.org/course/classicalcomp',6,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:42','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_classicalcomp','This course introduces students to strategies for style writing of common practice European art music.  The issues of harmonic progression, voice leading, and texture are addressed in addition to relevant compositional concepts like repetition, variation, and elaboration.  The course aims to offer a creative space even within the restrictions of stylistic emulation.','Music, Film, and Audio'),(1165,'Unpredictable? Randomness, Chance and Free Will',1,1,NULL,'https://www.coursera.org/course/randomness',8,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:42','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_randomness','This cross-disciplinary course deals with the undetermined, the unpredictable- or what appears to be such. Learn about the usefulness of randomness in communication and computation, the intrinsic randomness of quantum phenomena, the unpredictability of the weather, the role of chance in evolution, and the implications of the neural activity of the brain on our \"free will\".','Statistics and Data Analysis Physics'),(1166,'Matemáticas y movimiento',1,1,'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QmR2dt0u2Sk','https://www.coursera.org/course/precalculo',14,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:42','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_precalculo','El curso propone un acercamiento a la Matemática Preuniversitaria donde el contexto del movimiento en línea recta dará significado al conocimiento y la tecnología será el medio para interactuar con el mismo.','Mathematics'),(1167,'Egiptología (Egyptology)',1,1,'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=APL1bTMJb2U','https://www.coursera.org/course/egypt',8,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:42','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_egypt','Este curso introduce a los estudiantes de grado de habla hispana en los aspectos más relevantes de la lengua, la historia y la cultura del Egipto de los faraones.','Humanities '),(1168,'Pre-Calculus',1,1,'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=a2EIZuboBKU','https://www.coursera.org/course/precalc',8,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:42','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_precalc','Se trata de un curso pensado para facilitar la entrada del estudiante en los cursos de cálculo de primer semestre de prácticamente cualquier grado universitario, con especial  énfasis en Ciencias e Ingeniería. ','Mathematics'),(1169,'Histología básica: los cuatro tejidos fundamentales ',1,1,NULL,'https://www.coursera.org/course/histologia',NULL,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:42','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_histologia','Este curso está diseñado para que los estudiantes adquieran los conocimientos necesarios para distinguir los cuatro tipos de tejidos celulares que conforman el organismo. Está dirigido a estudiantes de Medicina, Biología, Veterinaria, Fisioterapia y Enfermería','Health & Society Biology & Life Sciences'),(1170,'Science, Technology, and Society in China II: History of S&T in Chinese Society',1,1,'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8L_6eMV-Fg0','https://www.coursera.org/course/stschina2',3,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:43','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_stschina2','This course is the second in a trilogy of short courses. In this part, we apply some of the concepts we covered in Part I to study the development of science and technology in Chinese society, particularly in light of the influence the Industrial Revolution in the West has had on China’s technological development.','Social Sciences'),(1171,'The Future of Humankind',1,1,NULL,'https://www.coursera.org/course/humankindfuture',NULL,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:43','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_humankindfuture','This course will take students on an extraordinary journey – the beginning of a massive transformation of humankind. Nothing remotely like this had ever happened in the billions of years of evolution on Earth. It was enabled by technology, but many other factors were part of its driving force.','Humanities '),(1172,'Guinea Pigs, Heroes & Desperate Patients: The History & Ethics of Human Research',1,1,NULL,'https://www.coursera.org/course/humanresearch',NULL,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:43','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_humanresearch','Learn about the ethical issues that arise when conducting human subjects research, as well as the history that grounds policies and debates in this area of biomedicine.','Medicine Humanities  Health & Society Biology & Life Sciences Social Sciences'),(1173,'The Science of Safety in Healthcare',1,1,NULL,'https://www.coursera.org/course/healthcaresafety',5,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:43','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_healthcaresafety','This course will introduce the basic principles of the science of safety in healthcare.  Course content will be of relevance to members of the healthcare delivery team, including nurses, as well as the healthcare consumers in the general public.  ','Medicine Health & Society'),(1174,'First-Year Composition 2.0',1,1,'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Pt2VJzUqUBk','https://www.coursera.org/course/gtcomp',8,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:43','2013-04-29 06:43:43','coursera_gtcomp','First-Year Composition 2.0 will help you to develop a better process and gain confidence in written, visual, and oral communication and to create and critique college-level documents and presentations.','Humanities '),(1175,'Science, Technology, and Society in China III: The Present & Policy Implications',1,1,'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8L_6eMV-Fg0','https://www.coursera.org/course/stschina3',3,NULL,'2013-04-29 06:43:43','2013-04-29 06:43:44','coursera_stschina3','This course is the third in a trilogy of short courses. In this final part, we integrate what we have learned in the previous two parts to investigate the evolution and implications of Chinese government policies designed to promote scientific and technological progress. Based on this, we will attempt to sketch a picture of the future of science and technology in China.','Social Sciences');
